@database REMLIB
@FONT COURIER.FONT 13
@INDEX "index.guide/main"
@NODE Main "REMLIB"
@TOC "rexx.guide/Built-In FUNCTION LIBRARY INDEX"
@{b}REMLIB()@{ub}

Usage:@{b}REMLIB(name)@{ub}

Removes an entry with the given name from @{"the Library List" LINK "rexx.guide/THE LIBRARY LIST"} maintained by the
resident process. The boolean return is 1 if the entry was found and
successfully removed. Note that this function does not make a distinction
between function libraries and function hosts, but simply removes a named entry.

See also: @{"ADDLIB()" LINK "ADDLIB/main"}

Example:
@{fg shine}
        say remlib('MyLibrary.library')  ==>1
@{fg text}
@ENDNODE
